\section{Theta functions and Riemann identity}\label{Theta functions and Riemann identity}


In this section we present some formulas which are useful for our computations. 
Assuming $1\gg {u}_I  \ge 0$ as well as the ``triangular inequality" $\sum_I {u}_I  \ge 2 {u}_K$ we have 
\begin{eqnarray}
&& \vartheta_1(v) = (z^{+1/2} - z^{-1/2}) q^{1/8} \prod_{n=1}^\infty (1-q^n) (1-z q^n) (1-z^{-1} q^n)\\
&& \vartheta_1(u_I) = - q^{1/8-{a}_I /2} (1 - q^{{a}_I }) \prod_{n=1}^\infty (1-q^n) (1- q^{n+{a}_I }) (1- q^{n-{a}_I })
\end{eqnarray}
as well as 
\begin{eqnarray}
&&\vartheta_1\left({1\over 2} (v+\epsilon\sum_I u_I)\right) = - \epsilon z^{-\epsilon/4} q^{1/8 - \sum_I {a}_I /4} (1 - z^{\epsilon /2}q^{\sum_I {a}_I /2}) \\
&&~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ \times \prod_{n=1}^\infty (1-q^n) (1-z^{\epsilon /2} q^{n+\sum_I {a}_I /2}) (1-z^{-\epsilon /2} q^{n-\sum_I {a}_I /2}) {\nonumber}\\
&&\vartheta_1\left({1\over 2} (v+\epsilon\sum_I u_I) - \epsilon u_K\right) = - \epsilon z^{-\epsilon/4} q^{1/8 - \sum_I {a}_I /4 + {a}_K/2} 
(1 - z^{\epsilon/2}q^{\sum_I {a}_I /2- {a}_K}) \\
&&~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~  \times \prod_{n=1}^\infty (1-q^n) (1-z^{\epsilon/2} q^{n+\sum_I {a}_I /2 -{a}_K}) 
(1-z^{-\epsilon/2} q^{n-\sum_I {a}_I /2 + {a}_K}){\nonumber}
\end{eqnarray}

The Riemann identity for the even spin structures reads 
\begin{eqnarray}
&&\sum_{a, {\rm even}} \vartheta_a(v) \vartheta_a(u_1) \vartheta_a(u_2) \vartheta_a(u_3)=  

\sum_{\epsilon=-1,1} \vartheta_1\left({1\over 2} (v+ \epsilon\sum_I u_I)\right) \prod_K \vartheta_1\left({1\over 2} (v-\epsilon\sum_I u_I + \epsilon u_K) \right){\nonumber}\\
\end{eqnarray}




